Personal Finance Management App
Features:
Expense Tracking:

Users can log their expenses and categorize them (e.g., food, transport, entertainment).
Income Tracking:

Users can log their income sources and amounts.
Budgeting:

Set up monthly or weekly budgets and track spending against these budgets.
Financial Goals:

Users can set and track financial goals (e.g., saving for a vacation, paying off debt).
Reports and Analytics:

Generate visual reports and charts to analyze spending patterns and financial health.
Recurring Transactions:

Manage recurring expenses and income (e.g., subscriptions, salaries).
Notifications and Alerts:

Get reminders for upcoming bills or when nearing budget limits.
Multi-Currency Support:

Track expenses and income in different currencies with automatic conversion.
Technologies:
Frontend: React for the user interface, using libraries like Chart.js or D3.js for visualizations.
Backend: Node.js with Express for handling API requests.
Database: MongoDB or SQL database to store user data, transactions, and financial goals.
Authentication: Use JWT (JSON Web Tokens) for user authentication and session management.
External APIs: Integrate with financial APIs for currency conversion or fetching real-time financial data.